node.text: Is it something that can help you build the future of your dreams? We only have a solid 14 hours of productive time during each day. Stop wasting it on things that aren’t making you better, aren’t making you money, and aren’t making you happy. When you think of saying you don’t have time. Think about the 53 or 140 hours you are wasting with inefficiencies in your life. You will always make time for what you really want.

node.title: What are you investing your time in?

node.text:
If you expect your life to change without putting in the work or making the sacrifices necessary to see progress, you’re going to be disappointed every time. Take a look at the things holding you back, and ask yourself: am I doing everything I possibly can to create success for myself and my family?
Thank you @wintheday.365 for joining us tonight and leaving us with such wisdom and knowledge

node.text: Whatever you want to see flourish and grow is what you’ll make time for. You family, your business, your mental health, your friends, etc. Stop making excuses for the things you know will be beneficial in the long run. Tell someone your game plan, get yourself an accountability partner, and keep making moves! #empowercouple #empowersquad

node.text:
Anyone that knows me, knows I am not a fan of Valentines Day. I know it’s a romantic holiday, but I personally would rather celebrate Love with @ximenaduque everyday of the year.  Not just take one day and recognize or treat special the one I love. 
Now let’s talk about how this beautiful soul is a Warrior.  A warrior is someone that is very strong and doesn’t give up easily.  The last month has been difficult and she needed to be a warrior. Not only a warrior an example to me, @carabiascristan, and @lunaadkins3. I would also say our hero. Child birth is one of the most difficult things that a women does. (Thank goodness men don’t have to, because our planet would be empty.) Happy valentines our way baby. To 364 more days of our actual  Valentines Year.. Thank you for @lunaadkins3 and @skyeadkins_3 the best valentines year present anyone could ask for. #itotallyhitthelottery.

node.text:
We’re all capable of inspiring and uplifting the people around us. But before you you can do that, you have to get over the fear of “what are they saying about me?”. 
Trust me, nobody is worried about what you’re doing because they’re too busy worried about what they’re doing! Get out of your shell and out of your comfort zone. You never know who’s life you might change!

node.text: The idea that pain is inevitable sounds miserable. But if you think about it, it's actually pretty liberating that we get to CHOOSE the kind of pain we’re willing to endure, instead of cowering in fear. Will you choose the pain of discipline, which only weighs ounces? Or will you choose the pain of regret, which is a heavy burden that sticks with you?

node.text: Whenever things aren’t going as planned or you hit a bump in the road, look for the silver lining. Find the positive things that are going to build you up and make you better when you come out on the other side of your situation. Keep pushing through! This twist in your story is going to end up leveling you up!

node.text: If you want something, work for it like someone is trying to beat you to it. Create that sense of urgency in the back of your mind and don’t let up until you’re where you want to be. And then....do it again.

node.text: Is it something that can help you build the future of your dreams? We only have a solid 14 hours of productive time during each day. Stop wasting it on things that aren’t making you better, aren’t making you money, and aren’t making you happy. When you think of saying you don’t have time. Think about the 53 or 140 hours you are wasting with inefficiencies in your life. You will always make time for what you really want.

node.text:
If you expect your life to change without putting in the work or making the sacrifices necessary to see progress, you’re going to be disappointed every time. Take a look at the things holding you back, and ask yourself: am I doing everything I possibly can to create success for myself and my family?
Thank you @wintheday.365 for joining us tonight and leaving us with such wisdom and knowledge

node.text: Sometimes NOT hitting the goal is the goal. Plan for it and shoot for it, but if you miss it, ask yourself: What did I learn that will help me hit it the next time around? As long as you’re not quitting, you’re winning.

node.text: Whatever you want to see flourish and grow is what you’ll make time for. You family, your business, your mental health, your friends, etc. Stop making excuses for the things you know will be beneficial in the long run. Tell someone your game plan, get yourself an accountability partner, and keep making moves! #empowercouple #empowersquad

node.text: @ximenaduque and I have been working so hard empowering others and building a business together. It has been stressful at times, but rewarding all the time. These moments that we capture is what makes the grind worth it. I just love the happiness i see in their eyes. These two are so beautiful to me. I’m so grateful for the life that I have. I love @ximenaduque and @lunaadkins3 so much. #empowercouple #lovemyfamily

node.text: I have always dreamed of having a partner like @ximenaduque and empowering people to live a better life. Now we have an empower squad to help us on this journey and this mission.  Join us on this journey and see how you can live the life of your dreams too. #empowercouple #EC2 #empowersquad @kikefloresphoto

node.text: Happy Fathers Day!! Late post because I spent every possible second with my girls. All I want on this day is Hugs, kisses, and snuggles. Father’s Day for me is  about my kids. Celebrating my biggest blessing. My beautiful wife @ximenaduque made my day so special by allowing me to do whatever I want, which she knows that’s time with my babies, holding them, kissing them, just being with them. I wasn’t always the best father in the beginning of fatherhood.  But I learned a long the way.  I love all of my babies so much. Jordan, @carabiascristan @lunaadkins3 @skyeadkins_3 Being a father is the most important thing I do. It’s my favorite thing in the whole entire world.
